            <fr:p>Let <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[X]]></fr:tex> be a compact Kähler variety (for example, smooth and projective).
    By the holomorphic Poincaré lemma, the de Rham complex <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Omega _X^\bullet ]]></fr:tex> is a resolution of the constant sheaf <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathbb {C}]]></fr:tex>.
    We thus have an isomorphism (<fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.4.2" href="hodge-theory-ii-1.4.2.xml" number="1.4.2" />)
    <fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[       \operatorname {H}^\bullet (X,\mathbb {C})       \sim  \operatorname {\mathbb {H}}^\bullet (X,\Omega _X^\bullet )     ]]></fr:tex>
    and the stupid filtration on <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\Omega _X^\bullet ]]></fr:tex> (<fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-1.4.5" href="hodge-theory-ii-1.4.5.xml" number="1.4.5" />) defines the hypercohomology spectral sequence

    <fr:tree toc="true" numbered="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" expanded="true" root="false" xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>479</fr:anchor><fr:addr type="user">hodge-theory-ii-2.2.1.1</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-ii-2.2.1.1.xml</fr:route><fr:taxon>Equation</fr:taxon><fr:authors /><fr:number>2.2.1.1</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-ii-2.2.1</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:tex display="block"><![CDATA[         E_1^{pq}         = \operatorname {H}^q(X,\Omega _X^q)         \Rightarrow  \operatorname {H}^{p+q}(X,\mathbb {C})       \tag{2.2.1.1}       ]]></fr:tex></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree>

    which abuts to the <fr:em>Hodge filtration</fr:em> of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^\bullet (X,\mathbb {C})]]></fr:tex>.</fr:p>
            <fr:p>By Hodge theory [<fr:link type="local" href="H1952.xml" addr="H1952" title="The theory and applications of harmonic integrals">H1952</fr:link>; <fr:link type="local" href="W1958.xml" addr="W1958" title="Introduction à L'Étude des Variétés Kählériennes">W1958</fr:link>], we have:

    
 <html:ol xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(A) &quot;">
        The spectral sequence <fr:ref addr="hodge-theory-ii-2.2.1.1" href="hodge-theory-ii-2.2.1.1.xml" taxon="Equation" number="2.2.1.1" /> degenerates: <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[E_1=E_\infty ]]></fr:tex>.
      </html:li>

      
 <html:li style="list-style-type: &quot;(B) &quot;">
        The Hodge filtration of <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[\operatorname {H}^n(X,\mathbb {C})]]></fr:tex> is <fr:tex display="inline"><![CDATA[n]]></fr:tex>-opposite to the complex conjugate filtration.
      </html:li>

    </html:ol></fr:p>
